ual property in the artworld and vice versa. Using real-life examples of artists who have incorporated copyrighted works into their art, he explores issues of artistic creation and the nature of infringement as they are informed by analytical aesthetics and legal and critical theory. Ultimately, Artistic License provides a critical and systematic analysis of the key philosophical issues that underlie copyright policy, rethinking the relationship between artist, artwork, and the law.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aAppropriation (Arts) 0aAppropriation (Arts). 0aAuthorshipxPhilosophy. 0aCopyrightxMoral rights. 0aCopyrightxPhilosophy. 0aCopyrightzUnited States. 0aCopyrightszUnited States. 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.) 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.). 0aFair use (Copyright) 0aFair use (Copyright). 0aMoral copyright. 4aAesthetics. 4aAppropriation. 4aArt. 4aArtistic Practice. 4aCopyright. 4aFair Use. 4aIntellectual Property. 4aOntology. 4aPhilosophy. 4aRemix. 70(DE-601)1042696690(DE-588)4172836-1aOriginalität2gnd 70(DE-601)1046232840(DE-588)4130545-0aAutorschaft2gnd 70(DE-601)10565454X0(DE-588)4136832-0aGeistiges Eigentum2gnd 70(DE-601)1058229570(DE-588)4114333-4aKunst2gnd 70(DE-601)1060853440(DE-588)4075660-9aOntologie2gnd 70(DE-601)1061334460(DE-588)4062127-3aUrheberrecht2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226460383423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226460383.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles